F4A-4 — List Staged CPs
Add a new action inside Prior Gates Incomplete → If No branch. Microsoft Dataverse → List rows.
Table: Staged Records
Filter rows: fx → concat('_pei_importcycle_value eq ', variables('varImportCycleID'), ' and pei_entitytype eq 890920000')
Rename to: List Staged CPs
Note: Entity Type = Control Procedure (890920000). We want ALL Staged CP records for this cycle (New, Updated, Removed, Reactivated) — every one of them needs its CP flagged Reviewed = Yes.

F4A-5 — Loop Staged CPs
Add an Apply to each inside If No, after List Staged CPs.
Select output: fx → outputs('List_Staged_CPs')?['body/value']
Rename to: Loop Staged CPs

F4A-6 — Find CP Record
Inside Loop Staged CPs. Dataverse → List rows.
Table: Control Procedures
Filter rows: fx → concat('pei_controlprocedureidentifier eq ''', items('Loop_Staged_CPs')?['pei_name'], '''')
Rename to: Find CP Record
Note: Staged Record's pei_name holds the CP Identifier text. This lookup resolves it to the actual CP GUID so we can update the CP.

F4A-7 — Condition: CP Found
Inside Loop Staged CPs, after Find CP Record.
Left: fx → length(outputs('Find_CP_Record')?['body/value'])
Operator: is greater than
Right: 0
Rename to: CP Found

F4A-8 — Update CP Reviewed
Inside CP Found → If Yes. Dataverse → Update a row.
Table name: Control Procedures
Row ID: lightning bolt → expand "Find CP Record" → select Control Procedure (the GUID dynamic content, not _pei_xxx_value). Do NOT use fx — that returns null (Error #26/31).
Reviewed: Yes (dropdown — boolean)
Leave every other field blank.
Rename to: Update CP Reviewed
